ce of viewing this aspect of the problem in a broader regional, even global, social and political context. Part two consists largely of fieldwork material which support and augment the conclusions of the preceding part. Part Three is a case study of the important petroleum-refining industry, and highlights its role in Singapore's overall economic growth. The fourth, a field study of the perceptions held by one group of small local businessmen (the motor fuel retailers, toward the oil companies) suggests the importance of cultural factors in the understanding of the evolving situation which follows upon the large-scale influx of foreign investment. Concludes with a basically reflective paper on the wider social and political ramifications of foreign investment in Singapore.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Government & Business.2bisacsh1 aArumugam, Raja Segaran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoo-Jock, Lim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLin, Lim Yoon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aM. Siddayao, Corazon, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSiddayao, Corazon M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoon Lin, Lim, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Archive eBook-Package 1970-1999z978311060669040uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981437637240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814376372423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814376372.jpg  a978-3-11-060669-0  ISEAS Archive eBook-Package 1970-1999c1970d1999  a978-3-11-064968-0  Asi